      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And there came a man of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Whether this is the same person as the \"prophet\" of vers. 13, 22, is not quite clear. The difference in the designation (see on 1 Kings 13:1 and p. 303) would lead us to suppose that a different messenger was meant. It is true the Hebrew has the article \"the man of God\" (LXX. ",
        "children": []
      },
